{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"12145","heading":"Temporary relief where lifts are unavailable","label":"12145 Temporary relief where lifts are unavailable","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch126/schII/ptB/spti","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs12145","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection effective , see , set out as a note under .July 26, 1990section 231(b) of Pub. L. 101–336section 12141 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Granting","label":"a Granting","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs12145%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs12145%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that the initial solicitation for new buses made by the public entity specified that all new buses were to be lift-equipped and were to be otherwise accessible to and usable by individuals with disabilities;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs12145%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the unavailability from any qualified manufacturer of hydraulic, electromechanical, or other lifts for such new buses;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs12145%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that the public entity seeking temporary relief has made good faith efforts to locate a qualified manufacturer to supply the lifts to the manufacturer of such buses in sufficient time to comply with such solicitation; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs12145%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that any further delay in purchasing new buses necessary to obtain such lifts would significantly impair transportation services in the community served by the public entity.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Duration and notice to Congress","label":"b Duration and notice to Congress","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs12145%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any relief granted under subsection (a) shall be limited in duration by a specified date, and the appropriate committees of Congress shall be notified of any such relief granted.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Fraudulent application","label":"c Fraudulent application","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs12145%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs12145%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"cancel such relief if such relief is still in effect; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12145/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs12145%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"take such other action as the Secretary considers appropriate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
